summary: This is just my ENB, it has been optimized mostly for Nvidia Cards since only have that type of card to try the ENB on. Feel free to tell others about it and upload images.
descriptionHtml:
[color=#ff0000][size=5]
[/size][/color]Requirements
ENB v0.266

Installation
1. Download [url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0266.htm]ENB v0.266[/url] and extract [size=2]ONLY[/size][size=3] [/size][size=2]the [b][u]d3d9.dll[/u][/b] and the [b][u]enbhost.exe[/u][/b] from [b][u]wrapper version[/u][/b] to your skyrim folder.
[/size]2. Download Rustic ENB and open the file and extract all files into your skyrim folder
3. Add (or modify) these lines to your skyrimPrefs.ini file (located by default in gt;Documents>My Games>skyrim) bFloatPointRender Target-1 bTreesReceiveShadows 1 bDrawLandShadows31 bShadowsOn Grass-1
4. Start your skyrimLauncher, disable Anti-Aliasing and Anisotropic Filtering
5. Start skyrim and enjoy this beautiful enb

I have only tested the ENB on nvidia cards but let me know if you experience any type of issues and I will try to fix it as soon as possible.
If you are going to use it in any type of video or photo on a website I would appreciate if you would credit me. But you are free to upload any screenshots on how your game look with my ENB in the image gallery here on the page.

http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/Images/512190/?For any questions send them to my steam profile [url=http://steamcommunity.com/id/Ghostwokiee/]Steam Profile here
[/url] ( I do not add people).
